<introduction>

	<objectives>
		<introduction>
			<p>
				After this chapter, you will be able to ...
			</p>
		</introduction>
		<ol>
			<li> Identify whether a DE is homogeneous. </li>
			<li> Identify whether a DE has constant coefficients. </li>
			<li> Solve a DE that is linear and has contant coefficients. </li>
		</ol>
	</objectives>

	<p>
		In this chapter, we delve into a powerful method known as "Undetermined Coefficients," tailored for tackling linear differential equations with constant coefficients.
	</p>

	<exploration xml:id="uc-method"><title> Undetermined Coefficients </title>
		<p>
			The general solution to the differential equation
			<men xml:id="uc-method-de">
				a_n\ y^{(n)} + a_{n-1}\ y^{(n-1)} + \cdots + a_2\ y'' + a_1\ y' + a_0\ y = f(x),
			</men>
			has a homogeneous part, <m>y_h\ </m>, and particular part, <m>y_p\ </m>, given by
			<men xml:id="uc-method-gen-soln">
				y = y_h + y_p,
			</men>
			and can be solved through the following steps...
		</p>
		<dl width="narrow">
			<li xml:id="uc-step1"><title>Step 1: Verify Method </title>
				<p>
					Check that the DE is linear and has constant coefficients.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li xml:id="uc-step2"><title>Step 2: Find <m>y_h</m> </title>
				<p>
					Use the LHCC Method on <xref ref="lhcc-eqn"/> to find <m>y_h</m>. 
				</p>
			</li>
			<li xml:id="uc-step3"><title>Step 3: Guess <m>y_p</m> </title>
				<p>
					Guess the form of <m>y_p</m> based on the form of <m>f(x)</m>.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li xml:id="uc-step4"><title>Step 4: Find <m>y_p</m> </title>
				<p>
					Plug <m>y_p</m> into <xref ref="uc-method-de"/> and solve for the unknown coefficients.
				</p>
			</li>
			<li xml:id="uc-step5"><title>Step 5: Give Solution </title>
				<p>
					Write down the general solution and apply initial conditions.
				</p>
			</li>
		</dl>
	</exploration>

</introduction>
